Iâ€™m not ready for the 2030s, ainâ€™t no way 2020 will be 6 years ago, I remember when 2014 was 6 years ago and we all saw how fast 6 turned to 10 years now. How is 2016 going to be 10 years ago next year, it was just 4 years ago??!! I started elementary school in September 2015, take me back! I hate high school so much. 2010 - 2019 was so peak. Mainly 2012 - 2016, then 2014 - 2017. I miss Summer 2012 - Summer 2018. Take me back please, I hate 2025, this year sucks so much. Take me to a place that I once knew that was filled with happiness and thrill and everything was possible. I went through so much these past 2 years since 2020. I'm only 15 and I remember all of these, I started elementary school in September 2015 and graduated in June 2020, lol. That virtual graduation was so miserable, but these memories are coming back, my favorite school years would have to be 2015 - 2016 (Kindergarten), 2016 - 2017 (First Grade), and 2017 - 2018 (Second Grade), mainly because all of my teachers gave me best memories of my life/childhood and most of my friend group started from here. I seriously wish I could go back, I remember when the Fidget Spinner trend was popping out in 2016 and 2017 the teachers got annoyed with us about it, but we didn't care. After we watched Madagascar (chosen by me since it's one of my favorite movie franchises). I remember when Despacito came out, me and my friends entered a talent show and performed. I can't believe that was June 2017 and June 2018, I miss those days and I pray for those days to come back once more.
